  "title": "Chef (Korean Cuisine)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Working Location: </strong>West, Singapore<br /><strong>Working Hours:</strong> 5-day work week (7am to 5pm) <br /><strong>Monthly Salary: </strong>Up to S$5K (Negotiable) <br /></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Expert in the preparation and execution of diverse Korean dishes.</li><li>Plans the monthly menu and works with Marketing on prints.</li><li>Cook and guide the kitchen team to cook according to the correct number of portions for each meal period, without wastage.</li><li>Ensure the freshness and quality of ingredients used and dishes served.</li><li>Ensure that the kitchen area is always kept clean and dry.</li><li>Maintain supplies to ensure adequate but not over-order, and no wastage.</li><li>Checking of goods receivable from suppliers.</li><li>Practice good food hygiene and safety standards.</li><li>Inspects and checks operating equipment to ensure good working conditions.</li><li>Interact with clients and gather feedback.</li><li>Check clients’ satisfaction and provide immediate updates to the Operations Manager and team.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 2–3 years of experience in preparing authentic Korean cuisine.</li><li>Knowledge of Korean ingredients, cooking techniques, and presentation.</li><li>Ability to work independently and manage kitchen operations.</li><li>Strong sense of hygiene, safety, and food quality standards.</li></ul><p><br />Nextbeat Singapore Pte. Ltd.</p><p>EA License Number: 22C1267</p><p>EA Personnel No: R22107133</p><p></p>",
